<paragraph id="8BA59702484D29296FC8544A98904184" blockId="24.[151,1436,1820,2006]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1436,152,618]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Body and legs homogeneously cream-coloured. Anterior eye row procurved, eyes of similar size, laterals projecting ventrally. Posterior eyes of similar size, slightly larger than anterior eyes. Femur I with nine pairs of ventral thin spines. Tibia I with five pairs of ventral spines. Tibia I with long and curved dorsal and lateral tri- chobothria. Total length 8.0. Carapace 2.9 long, 2.4 wide. Tibia I length 5.8, II 5.5, III 3.3, IV 3.6. Opisthosoma 5.1 long, 1.1 wide. The embolus apex is wide, flattened and notched (
<figureCitation id="13218B87484C29296B0453E698654184" box="[1035,1142,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="24.[151,269,1646,1670]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,191,1604]" captionTargetId="figure-125@24.[135,1452,150,1648]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Architis helveola (Simon). A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, male pedipalpus, ventral view; C, male pedipalpus, lateral view; D, female epigynum, ventral view; E, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B–C, 0.2 mm; D–E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097209/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
